Retchmail v0.1
Release Date: January 2002
Authors: Avery Pennarun <apenwarr@nit.ca>
         Patrick Patterson <ppatters@nit.ca>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Retchmail is intended as a blazingly fast replacement for ESR's Fetchmail.
For a much more in depth overview of the philosophy behind this program,
please read apenwarr's ANNOUNCEment for the program, which should be
found in the same directory as this file.

For a quick overview of the functionality, please see the retchmail(1) man
page, which should get you started.

Questions, comments, feature requests, and especially patches should be
directed to the retchmail mailing list:

retchmail-list@lists.nit.ca

This program is Copyright 2002-2003 Net Integration Technologies Inc.

This program is licensed under the LGPL, a full copy of which can be found
in the COPYING.LIB file in the same directory as this file.
